<paragraph id="0703185BFF9EFF89B994FE650856FBE5" blockId="21.[163,779,842,1048]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF9EFF89B994FE650B0AFCA2" box="[163,604,842,864]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF9EFF89B873FE640B0AFCA2" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[324,604,842,863]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galesus">Cnodocentron galesus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF9EFF89B994FE47083AFC83" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1991" box="[163,364,873,894]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculatum">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF9EFF89B994FE47083AFC83" box="[163,364,873,894]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">C. immaculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF9EFF89B89AFE470B4EFC83" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[429,536,873,894]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallas">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF9EFF89B89AFE470B4EFC83" box="[429,536,873,894]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">C. pallas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a pair of stout spines on the ventral projection of coxopodite. 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF9EFF89B994FE8808CEFC46" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[163,408,934,955]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galesus">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF9EFF89B994FE8808CEFC46" box="[163,408,934,955]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362">Cnodocentron galesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed by the truncate apical margin of sternum IX in lateral view; and the median region of coxopodite with a transverse patch of setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="53C348D3FF9EFF89BA0CFEBB0AACFC34" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461376" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6461376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461376/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="1362" startId="21.[827,912,917,939]" targetBox="[830,1439,196,877]" targetPageId="21">
